Take a look of the astounding architecture of the Los Angeles Central Library
A salon will be hosted by Southern California Branch of Society of Architectural Historians and the co-authors of Los Angles Central Museum: Art and Architectural History, Arnold Schwarzman and Stephen Gee. It will deliver more knowledge of the Central Library to the participants.
Gee and Schwarzman will discuss and share images of design by Bertram Goodhue in 1926 and restoration and expansion of  Hardy Holzman Pfeiffer Associates in 1933.
The salon hours are: 2pm to 4pm, August 21. Address: Salle Moderne, Art Deco Southwestern School of Law (formerly Bullocks Wilshire), 3050 Wilshire Blvd.
Visitors can visit the venues of the central hall, the history exhibit, the cactus lounge, and the tea lounge.
Advance ticket reservation required; SAHSCC members: US$15; non-members: US$25.
A comfortable makeover was provided to the open factory building design of DTLA.
